      "body": "Question: `LookupFilterRange()` calls `filters_out.resize(entries.size())`, which now allocates a `GCSFilter` object for each default-constructed `BlockFilter`, only to have it immediately replaced by the filter read from disk.\n\nBefore this PR, default construction already allocated the encoded vector, so the extra allocation is probably small compared to disk I/O. Still, this looks like an added cost of having `BlockFilter` own the filter through the new abstraction. Is this a worthwhile trade-off given the extensibility goals here?",
